# Entity: User

## Description
Represents a registered user in the system. Users can authenticate via OAuth providers ({% for method in auth_methods %}{{ method }}{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}) and access the application across all platforms.

## Fields

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| id | UUID | Yes | Primary key |
| email | String | Yes | Email address (unique) |
| displayName | String | Yes | User's display name |
| avatarUrl | String | No | Profile picture URL |
| authProvider | String | Yes | Authentication provider ({% for method in auth_methods %}{{ method }}{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}) |
| authProviderId | String | No | ID from the OAuth provider |
| passwordHash | String | No | BCrypt hash (only for password auth) |
| role | Enum | Yes | User role: USER, ADMIN |
| isActive | Boolean | Yes | Account active status |
| lastLoginAt | DateTime | No | Last login timestamp |
| createdAt | DateTime | Yes | Account creation timestamp |
| updatedAt | DateTime | Yes | Last update timestamp |

## Relationships

- **has many** features-specific entities (defined per feature)

## Validation Rules

- `email`: must be valid email format, unique across all users
- `displayName`: 1-100 characters
- `authProvider`: must be one of the enabled providers
- `passwordHash`: required only when `authProvider` is "password"
- `role`: defaults to USER, can only be changed by admins

## Business Logic

- Users are created on first successful authentication
- If a user logs in with a new OAuth provider but same email, accounts are linked
- Admins can deactivate user accounts (sets `isActive` to false)
- Deactivated users cannot authenticate

## Database

- **Table name**: `users`
- **Indexes**: unique on `email`, index on `auth_provider`
- **Migration**: `V1__init.sql`

